Below is the full content for each file in MY portfolio project

1. index.html
This is the main HTML file for your portfolio website.

html
Copy code
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Ananthagari Venkata Balaji's Portfolio</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Hello, I am Ananthagari Venkata Balaji</h1>
        <p>Welcome to my portfolio website!</p>
    </header>

    <main>
        <!-- About Section -->
        <section id="about">
            <h2>About Me</h2>
            <p>
                I am a passionate developer and technology enthusiast currently pursuing B.Tech.
                I have experience in web development, AI, ML, and various other technical fields.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Experience Section -->
        <section id="experience">
            <h2>Experience</h2>
            <div class="scrollable-content">
                <p>I have worked on various projects, including:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Foot Step Power Generator project</li>
                    <li>Hackathons including NASA Space Apps Challenge</li>
                    <li>Internship at Teachnook focusing on AI/ML</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Courses Section -->
        <section id="courses">
            <h2>IT Courses</h2>
            <p>
                I offer several IT-related courses, including Data Science, Web Development, and more. Contact me for more details.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Contact Section -->
        <section id="contact">
            <h2>Get In Touch</h2>
            <p>Feel free to reach out to me via the links below!</p>
            <div class="contact-buttons">
                <button id="email-btn">Email</button>
                <button id="whatsapp-btn">WhatsApp</button>
                <button id="linkedin-btn">LinkedIn</button>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>Contact me at: <a href="mailto:your-email@example.com">your-email@example.com</a></p>
    </footer>

    <script src="js/scripts.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
2. css/styles.css
The main CSS file for styling your portfolio website.

css
Copy code
/* General Styles */
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    background-color: #f4f4f4;
    color: #333;
}

header {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #4CAF50, #2E8B57);
    color: white;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 2em 0;
}

h1, h2 {
    margin: 0.5em 0;
}

main {
    padding: 1em;
}

footer {
    text-align: center;
    background-color: #333;
    color: white;
    padding: 1em 0;
}

/* About Section */
#about {
    padding: 2em 0;
}

/* Experience Section */
#experience {
    padding: 2em 0;
}

.scrollable-content {
    max-height: 150px;
    overflow-y: auto;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    padding: 1em;
}

/* Courses Section */
#courses {
    padding: 2em 0;
}

/* Contact Section */
#contact {
    padding: 2em 0;
}

.contact-buttons button {
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    border: none;
    padding: 1em;
    color: white;
    margin: 0.5em;
    border-radius: 5px;
    cursor: pointer;
}

.contact-buttons button:hover {
    background-color: #45a049;
}

/* Scrolling */
::-webkit-scrollbar {
    width: 10px;
}

::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    border-radius: 5px;
}
3. js/scripts.js
Basic JavaScript for your website's interactivity.

javascript
Copy code
document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function() {
    // Contact buttons
    document.getElementById("email-btn").addEventListener("click", function() {
        window.location.href = "mailto:your-email@example.com";
    });

    document.getElementById("whatsapp-btn").addEventListener("click", function() {
        window.open("https://wa.me/your-whatsapp-number");
    });

    document.getElementById("linkedin-btn").addEventListener("click", function() {
        window.open("https://linkedin.com/in/your-profile");
    });
});
4. assets/
This folder will hold any additional files like fonts or icons that you might need.

5. images/
Place your profile image or other images used on your site in this folder. If you have a profile picture, reference it in the index.html like this:

html
Copy code
<img src="images/profile.jpg" alt="Your Profile Picture">
6. css/, js/
These folders already contain your styles.css and scripts.js.

Uploading Steps to GitHub:
Once your folder structure and file contents are ready:

Open Git Bash or any Git client.
Navigate to your project folder (MyFortfolio1).
Initialize Git, commit, and push to GitHub using the following commands:
bash
Copy code
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git remote add origin https://github.com/your-username/MyFortfolio-AnanthagariVenkataBalaji.git
git push -u origin master
Now your portfolio will be live on GitHub Pages once you set it as a GitHub Pages project! Let me know if you need more details.
